The paper discusses fair division methods in the context of redistricting, which involves the allocation of resources (in this case, political power) among multiple parties. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and mathematical models to achieve fair division, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the practical considerations of redistricting, such as incorporating multiple criteria for a good redistricting solution, which suggests that it may belong to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of rigorous guarantees for fairness, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
